Description: Fragment of neck and oval handle, to shoulder join, of a Cyrenaic pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine red-brown. Irregular rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 201, 45. For an interpretation of the stamp as 'BARKE' see Johnston, 'Fragmenta Britannica IV', Bull.Inst.Class.St. 57 (2014) 220-1.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1669)
